OL,6,FMarmont was charged the following day
OL,7,Fwith one count each of dangerous
OL,8,Fdriving, driving whilst disqualified
OL,9,Fand driving without insurance.
OL,11,FMarmont, from Witney, pleaded guilty
OL,12,Fwas sentenced to two years in prison
OL,13,Ffor dangerous driving and driving
OL,14,Fwhile disqualified.
OL,16,FInvestigating officer PC Liam Calvert,
OL,17,Fof the Joint Roads Policing Unit,
OL,18,Fsaid: "This conviction demonstrates
OL,19,Fthe seriousness of Marmont's driving,
OL,20,Fwhich fell far below that of a
OL,21,Fcompetent driver.
